Name: Queensway
Phrase: So this is Hinayashiki...

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Even if I expected it, but there are so many dolls here. There's a whole yard full of Nishikese dolls.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Is everyone alright?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Conductor and the others haven't arrived yet. It seems a bit late for them to have followed us right away...

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Sorry to keep you all waiting. Nishiki's sorceress is kenzan here.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: 'Yoshino! Thank goodness you're here. You're a bit late, I was worried.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Heroes always arrive late. Yuuzen and Shashou are with us.
After passing through the Gate that Yuuzen recreated, Hinayashiki appeared right in front of us. The Train Knights who went ahead of us were all safe.

As previously reported, there was a very thick Phantom Mist around Hinayashiki. The Mist was so thick that even Versailles could not confirm whether or not our current location was in fact the Hinayashiki. I felt this place to be similar to Iris Cloud's Sea of Mist.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: So this is Miyako's parents' house. It's quite a big mansion, eh? She must have been quite the ojou-sama.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: That joke's not funny.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: I didn't mean it as a joke.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Fortunately there is no thick Phantom Mist on the grounds of Hinayashiki. I think we can search the interiors. Let's hurry and look for Miss Miyako.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: This is Miyako's house. If we find Miyako, she will lead us to her master.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: The dolls here are also Miyako's friends. We'll be lucky if they cooperate.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Don't get yer hopes up. This isn't the house Miyako knows anymore. Ya should expect enemies everywhere.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: A skilled sorceress is on the other side. There's a possibility that we've already fallen for the tricks.
Don't touch my child. Once you abandon a doll, you can never live with it again.
I hate. I hate people. I hate people who throw away pretty dolls.
I hate. I hate mothers. I hate mothers who abandon their living children.
Don't worry. I won't let you feel that way. I will take care of you from now on.
I'll be with you all the time. You will live with me in this house forever.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: ...My my, looks like we're dealing with a nastier opponent than I thought.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Ya said ya're Versailles, I heard ya know a lot about Hinayashiki.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Yes, well. I know a lot about Miyako's time inside Hinayashiki...

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Well, before I ask for more details, I'll make a guess. On what kind of a person is Miyako's master.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: It was neither a person nor a doll that brought Miyako up in Hinayashiki. It was a monster living in the Mist that took the place of Miyako's mother, wasn't it?

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Monster... Miyako was raised by a demon?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Versailles, is it true?

Name: Versailles
Phrase: ...Yes. It's true.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Raised by a monster...?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Miyako, she never told me anything like that...

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Hinayashiki was famous as a place to throw away dolls with a history. There was a woman who lived there who loved dolls and she would take any doll she wanted.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: However, the owner of the mansion was not a person, but a monster. So a doll-loving monster lived in the house.'

Name: Putra
Phrase: Wait a minute. That monster is a doll-lover who collects dolls, right? If so, why did she raise Miyako?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Before that, why was Miyako even in Hinayashiki?

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Miyako was abandoned in Hinayashiki. She was buried under a pile of dolls and exposed to the wind and rain for many days.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: That's terrible...

Name: Putra
Phrase: I guess that means the monster saved her life.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: 'Yes. That's why Miyako still doesn't hold a grudge against the master. She saved her life and brought her up.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: But Miyako must face her master. Even if she saved her life, the monster waiting for us at the back of Hinayashiki is quite vicious.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Probably a lot different from when she was acting as Miyako's mother.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: How do you know so much? Maybe she's just possessed by something?

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: It doesn't matter if she's possessed or not. One look at that Gate and ya can tell that the caster is not a decent person.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: That Gate is an extremely problematic creation by the monster of Hinayashiki. If a weaker sorcerer handles it, he or she will lose his life. It's not something humans do. I wouldn't make something like that either.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: It has very strong negative feelings towards people. It is resentful, jealous, hateful and want to kill people. It can't forgive anyone who is happy except itself. I could feel these feelings through that Gate.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: And just now, the same demonic voice was heard from the back of the mansion just a few minutes ago. It's also tricky because it uses words but doesn't understand words.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: I don't understand why she picked up Miyako, who is a person, and raised her. She could have taken her and eaten her out of the blue.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: There's a bit of a complicated story about that. Miyako was not just an abandoned child...

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: If possible, I'd like you to tell me what the full story. It could be a clue for us as a strategy to attack Hinayashiki.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Miss Yoshino. I'm sure Miyako told you to 'ask Versailles for more information', yes?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yes. She said she wished she could have told me more about Hinayashiki.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Then I can tell you. Miyako's secret...

Name: Versailles
Phrase: When Miyako was abandoned here. Miyako was put under a strong curse, called 'Dollification'.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Dollification curse, it's a very scary curse that makes you think you're a doll.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Doesn't it mean that your body actually becomes like a doll?

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: There are two kinds of curses: one that turns you into a doll only in body, and one that turns you into a doll only in mind. The one that was applied to Miyako is the one that only turns her mind into a doll. She must have suffered a lot when she was brought up by the monster.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: They'll still get sick, they get hurt, and if they don't eat, they die.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Miyako was abandoned here as a doll and brought up here as a doll. She had the curse lifted by someone she loved like a sister. Miyako was on the verge of starvation at the time.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: With the help of her savior, Miyako escaped from Hinayashiki. But she had been living as a doll all her life. It took her a long time and a lot of training before she was able to live like a normal human being.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: See, you might find Miyako to be cold-hearted sometimes, right? That's because she doesn't understand human emotions yet. Just like with other people's emotions, she's still learning about her own emotions as well.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: The reason Miyako is not very emotional... is because she has none.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: It must have been very difficult for her to be brought up as a doll and then re-educated as a living being...

Name: Versailles
Phrase: I should have told you about this a little earlier, but I thought Miyako would tell you herself about this.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: It was her doll friend who helped Miyako...

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Miss Yoshino?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Miyako had a very clever doll friend. A child who can walk and speak by herself.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: She broke Miyako's curse. Miyako said, 'Thanks to her, I became a person again.'

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: The doll is very kind. She's very good. She told Miyako that her place was not here. She really wanted to be with Miyako all the time...

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: It's okay to stay together forever. If it's a relationship between a 'person' and a 'doll'...".

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: It is a twisted power that turns dolls into people and people into dolls. To wish people could love dolls and dolls could love people.
People lose their lives. People take their lives.
People hurt their dolls. But when they hurt themselves, they blame the dolls.
People go to the doll dump for fear of curses. People curse people, but everyone blames the dolls.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: It's the same voice as the one from earlier. She's definitely watching us.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Hey, Yuuzen. Yoshino's black doll is glowing.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Yoshino, gimme yer hand!

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Hand?
Yuuzen noticed something and asked Yoshino to hold out her hand. Yoshino did as he was told and held out her right hand towards Yuuzen. And...

Name: Versailles
Phrase: They're gone!

Name: Queensway
Phrase: What happened!? How could this happen with a Gate!
We were just about to begin our search inside Hinayashiki, two reliable sorceresses have disappeared at the same time...
